File: Former Springbok coach Peter de Villiers has been appointed Eastern Province Currie Cup coach for 2021. AFP/Simon Maina JOHANNESBURG - Peter de Villiers has made a comeback in the rugby coaching ranks.
The former Springbok coach has been appointed Eastern Province Currie Cup coach for 2021. READ: Peter de Villiers speaks on Black Lives Matter, GBV The outspoken De Villiers has often made it known that he struggled to secure coaching jobs after leaving the Springbok position. His appointment was made along with that of Ryan Felix, who'll take charge of the union's Under 20 team.